The fix addresses the issue where short text files were incorrectly identified as TAR archives. The problem was in the `createArchiveInputStream` method in `ArchiveStreamFactory.java` where there was a fallback mechanism (added for COMPRESS-117) that tried to determine if a stream was a TAR file by creating a `TarArchiveInputStream` and attempting to read an entry.

This fallback mechanism was causing false positives where non-TAR content (like plain text) was being incorrectly recognized as TAR files. The solution was to disable this problematic fallback code by commenting it out, ensuring that only proper TAR signature detection is used for auto-recognition.

The test `shortTextFilesAreNoTARs` now passes, confirming that short text files are no longer incorrectly treated as TAR archives, which fixes the COMPRESS-171 issue.

